2. We have identified an ability of organic matter in soils and sediments to trap uranium without the well-known chemical reduction, which inhibits its uptake into plant roots. We have also identified physiological mechanisms by whch plants limit transfer of uranium and radium into above-ground tissues.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>The findings should be usable by industry and regulators in the nuclear sector</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>03C1881B-6BB5-4AD7-A370-78065C6BDA66</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Energy,Environment</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs><gtr:policyInfluenceOutput><gtr:areas/><gtr:description>Nuclear Advisory Committees</gtr:description><gtr:geographicReach>National</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>C17BF777-3378-4E6E-AECA-5436FBCCF4C1</gtr:id><gtr:impact>Participation in a number of Government advisory committees, principally-

